title: NASA Awards Contract for NOAA’s Next-Generation Space Weather Sensors
description: NASA, on behalf of the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA), has selected Johns Hopkins University’s Applied Physics Laboratory of Laurel, Maryland, to build the Suprathermal Ion Sensors for the Lagrange 1 Series project, part of NOAA’s Space Weather Next Program. title: NASA, USAID Invite Media to Launch of New SERVIR Central America Hub
description: NASA and the U.S. Agency for International Development (USAID) invite media to the official launch celebration of the new SERVIR Central America regional hub, located in Costa Rica, on Tuesday, Dec. 3, at 11 a.m. EST. author: Lee Mohon

title: Super-bright black holes could reveal if the universe is pixelated
description: Space-time may not be continuous but instead made up of many discrete bits – and we may be able to see their effects near the edges of unusually bright black holes

title: Exploding interstellar space rocks could explain mystery radio flashes
description: Enigmatic phenomena called fast radio bursts might be caused by interstellar objects colliding with highly magnetised neutron stars

title: ‘Portal to space’: the place where astronauts take off and land – in pictures

title: Magnetic tornadoes on Jupiter are spawning Earth-size storms
description: Magnetic vortices twisting down from Jupiter's ionosphere into its deep atmosphere cause giant, ultraviolet-absorbing polar anticyclones, each the size of our Earth.
